# campaign-condition-model

Campaign Condition Core Components:

1. Condition Trigger System (Importance: 95)
- Multi-step condition verification workflow
- Sequential vs parallel condition evaluation
- Time-based delay conditions with configurable windows
- Automatic vs manual verification modes
- Condition dependency chains with rollback capabilities

2. Reward Distribution Engine (Importance: 90)
- Gift card allocation based on condition completion
- Inventory verification before reward commitment
- Multi-provider fallback for gift card provisioning
- Automatic retry mechanism for failed distributions
- Balance tracking across reward pools

3. Verification Rules (Importance: 85)
- Manual agent verification requirements
- Form submission validation logic
- Call completion tracking
- SMS confirmation workflows
- Multi-step approval chains

4. Time-Based Controls (Importance: 80)
- Configurable waiting periods between conditions
- Campaign-specific expiration rules
- Grace periods for condition completion
- Rate limiting for reward distribution
- Automated cleanup of expired conditions

5. Campaign Condition Types
- manual_agent: Requires agent verification
- crm_event: Triggered by CRM integrations 
- time_delay: Enforces waiting periods
- mail_delivered: Tracks physical mail status
- form_submitted: Validates form completions
- call_completed: Monitors call center activity

Core Business Rules:
- Conditions must complete in defined sequence
- Rewards locked until all conditions verified
- Manual verification requires specific agent roles
- Time delays enforce minimum waiting periods
- Failed conditions trigger automatic rollback

